==English==
===Etymology===
From [[hay]] + [[wire]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/'heɪwʌɪə/}}
*{{audio|en-us-haywire.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|haywire|haywires}}
# [[wire]] used to bind bales of [[hay]]

===Adjective===
{{en-ad|haywire}}
# roughly-made, unsophisticated, decrepit (from the use of haywire for temporary repairs)
# Behaving [[erratic]]ally or in an [[uncontrollable]] manner, especially of a [[machine]] or mechanical process.
#:''Everything was working fine until it suddenly went '''haywire''' and wouldn't stop printing blank sheets.''

